                    	<h1>EXPERT ANALYSIS</h1>
                        <h2>Commentary on the Iranian Nuclear Program</h2>
                        <div class="art">
                        	<a href="/assessments"><img src="/images/usebomb.jpg" /></a>
                            <h3>Would Iran Use the Bomb?</h3>
                            <p>Many theories abound for why Iran will never fulfill threats to use a nuclear bomb.</p>
                            <p>But do any of these theories hold water? Futhermore, if Iran reaches the nuclear threshhold, would it even need to actually use a nuclear weapon to influence events in the Middle East?</p>
                            <div class="detail_button_33"><a href="/assessments.html">LEARN MORE</a></div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="art">
                        	<a href="/miloptionanly"><img src="/images/option-icon.gif" /></a>
                            <h3>Military Option</h3>
                            <p>The time is rapidly approaching when dramatic steps beyond diplomacy - such as a last resort military strike - may be the only way to halt Iran's nuclear progress.</p>
                            <p>Besides the basic desire to avoid war, however, a number of factors mitigate against a military operation.</p>
                            <div class="detail_button_33"><a href="/miloptionanly.html">LEARN MORE</a></div>
                            <div class="viewmore2"><a href="/relatedtoc.html">More Analysis &raquo;</a></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
